<h1 class="heading-36">Can you get Carer's Allowance?</h1>

<p>You must meet all 4 of these requirements before you can get Carer's Allowance:<p>


<h3>1. Are you are aged 16 or over?</h3>
    <%= partial 'partials/questions/yes-no', :locals => { :id => '16_over'} %>

<h3>2. Do you live in England, Scotland or Wales?</h3>
<p>Families of HM Forces can apply from any country.
  If you live in Northern Ireland go to <a href="#">NI Carers Allowance</a>.</p>
    <%= partial 'partials/questions/yes-no', :locals => { :id => 'live_in'} %>

<h3>3. Do you care for someone for 35 hours a week or more?</h3>
<p>For example, cooking meals, or helping them with their shopping.</p>
    <%= partial 'partials/questions/yes-no', :locals => { :id => '35_hours'} %>

<h3>4. Does the person you care for get a disability benefit?</h3>

<p>They must get one of these benefits for you to get Carer's Allowance:</p>

    <div class="benefit-list">
      <ul class="list-bullet">
        <li><strong>Personal Independence Payment</strong> - the standard or enhanced rate of the Daily Living Component
        </li>
        <li><strong>Disability Living Allowance</strong> - the middle or highest rate</li>
    <li><strong>Attendance Allowance</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Constant Attendance Allowance</strong> - the Addition to Disablement Benefit at normal maximum rate or more, or <br> - the Addition to War Disablement Pension at full rate</li>
        <li><strong>Armed Forces Independence Payment</strong></li>
      </ul>

    </div>



    <%= partial 'partials/questions/yes-no', :locals => { :id => 'benefit_type'} %>



  <div id="failure" class="prompt" >

